```
SimpleDateFormat df;
if (hasLocale) {
    df = new SimpleDateFormat(df0.toPattern(), format.getLocale());
    // Preserve original timezone
    TimeZone origTz = df0.getTimeZone();
    if (origTz != null) {
        df.setTimeZone(origTz);
    }
} else {
    df = (SimpleDateFormat) df0.clone();
}
```
Then later:
```
TimeZone newTz = format.getTimeZone();
boolean changeTZ = (newTz != null) && !newTz.equals(df.getTimeZone());
if (changeTZ) {
    df.setTimeZone(newTz);
}
```

That preserves original timezone even if only locale changes.

